<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.2325/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-23T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">August 23,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:44
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>97. I have been requested by the Minister for Foreign Affairs to ask for
                            the good offices of the United States for the formal <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi> from the Government of Chile for Cesar A. Elguera as
                            Ambassador to Chile. As soon as I am informed of the receipt of the
                            Chilean reply, the name will be made public here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>